ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

0=Emergency Department; 1=48 Hours; 2=Week 1; 3=Week 2; 4=Week 3; 5=Week 4; 6=Week 5; 7=Week 6; 8=Week 7; 9=Week 8; 10=Month 3; 11=Month 6; 12=Month 9; 13=Month 12; 14= In-Person Deep Phenotyping Session
Randomly Assigned at enrollment, each group has different combination of battery for assessment # 2 onwards.

ElementDescription: Day since enrollment when the battery started
Total time to complete test (in seconds)
String containing information on device used

Notes: Note: input for this is ambiguous for some cases.

ElementDescription: Presence or absence of touchscreen input
Operating system category (of most frequently used OS)
